         <abstract>
            <p>Let K be the compositum of a real quadratic number field K&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; and a complex cubic number field K&lt;sub&gt;3&lt;/sub&gt;. Further, let ε be a unit of K which is also a relative unit with respect to K/K&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; and K/K&lt;sub&gt;3&lt;/sub&gt;. The absolute discriminant of this non-Galois sextic number field K is estimated from above by a simple, strictly increasing, polynomial function of ε. This estimate, which can be used to determine a generator for the cyclic group of relative units, substantially improves a similar bound due to Nakamula. The method employed makes nontrivial use of computer algebra techniques.</p>
          </abstract>
